The paper discusses various approaches involving machine learning, information theory, social network analysis, semantic web, and linked open data for music-related analysis. These approaches are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing), cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks), and cs.DB (Databases). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
